161 209 M 
-0.200 0 (                                         Doc No: X3J16/97-0085 WG21/N1123)A 
; : 161 254 1725 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 254 M 
-0.200 0 (                                         Date:   September 30th, 1997)A 
; : 161 299 1850 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 299 M 
-0.200 0 (                                         Project: Programming Language C++)A 
; : 161 344 1225 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 344 M 
-0.200 0 (                                         Ref Doc:)A 
; : 161 389 1575 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 389 M 
-0.200 0 (                                         Reply to: Josee Lajoie)A 
; : 161 434 1750 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 434 M 
-0.200 0 (                                                  \(josee@vnet.ibm.com\))A 
; : 161 569 1450 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 569 M 
-0.200 0 ( How should the keyword 'template' be added to the syntax?)A 
; : 161 614 1450 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 614 M 
-0.200 0 ( =========================================================)A 
; : 161 704 1000 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 704 M 
-0.200 0 ( A\) Adding 'template' to the C++ grammar)A 
; : 161 749 1000 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 749 M 
-0.200 0 (    ------------------------------------)A 
; : 161 839 1850 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 839 M 
-0.200 0 (   Core 3 noticed that the current C++ grammar does not support the use of)A 
; : 161 884 1825 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 884 M 
-0.200 0 (   the template keyword in all the places where subclause 14.2 says it is)A 
; : 161 929 1700 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 929 M 
-0.200 0 (   allowed.  For example, the following cases are not allowed by the)A 
; : 161 974 275 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 974 M 
-0.200 0 (   grammar:)A 
; : 161 1019 500 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1019 M 
-0.200 0 (   In qualified-ids:)A 
; : 161 1064 1075 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1064 M 
-0.200 0 (         A<T>::template B<X>::template C<Y>)A 
; : 161 1109 700 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1109 M 
-0.200 0 (               -------------)A 
; : 161 1154 750 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1154 M 
-0.200 0 (   In pseudo-destructor-calls:)A 
; : 161 1199 875 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1199 M 
-0.200 0 (         p->A::template B<T>::~B\(\);)A 
; : 161 1244 700 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1244 M 
-0.200 0 (               -------------)A 
; : 161 1334 1750 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1334 M 
-0.200 0 (   After discussions with Bill Gibbons, John Spicer, Anthony Scian and)A 
; : 161 1379 1800 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1379 M 
-0.200 0 (   myself, it seems that we cannot come to an agreement as to how to fix)A 
; : 161 1424 200 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1424 M 
-0.200 0 (   this.)A 
; : 161 1514 1500 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1514 M 
-0.200 0 (   Here are the two approaches that are under consideration:)A 
; : 161 1604 1800 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1604 M 
-0.200 0 (   A.1\) allow the template keyword in the template-name production, i.e.)A 
; : 161 1694 475 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1694 M 
-0.200 0 (      template-name)A 
; : 161 1739 850 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1739 M 
-0.200 0 (          template\(opt\) identifier)A 
; : 161 1829 1850 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1829 M 
-0.200 0 (      This is a simple grammar fix but it allows the 'template' keyword in)A 
; : 161 1874 1800 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1874 M 
-0.200 0 (      many more contexts than that currently allowed by chapter 14.  The)A 
; : 161 1919 1775 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1919 M 
-0.200 0 (      solution would be to prohibit the 'template' keyword to appear in)A 
; : 161 1964 1875 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1964 M 
-0.200 0 (      these additional contexts by adding additional semantics rules in the)A 
; : 161 2009 225 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2009 M 
-0.200 0 (      WP.)A 
; : 161 2099 1775 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2099 M 
-0.200 0 (   A.2\) apply the grammar change higher up in the grammar, to allow the)A 
; : 161 2144 1825 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2144 M 
-0.200 0 (      keyword template only in the places that are already allowed by the)A 
; : 161 2189 1750 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2189 M 
-0.200 0 (      text in chapter 14.  This means that a greater number of grammar)A 
; : 161 2234 1800 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2234 M 
-0.200 0 (      rules must be changed and there is the possibility that we did not)A 
; : 161 2279 550 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2279 M 
-0.200 0 (      cover all cases.)A 
; : 161 2369 1600 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2369 M 
-0.200 0 (     2.1\) Add "template" to the *middle* of the grammar rule for)A 
; : 161 2414 975 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2414 M 
-0.200 0 (          nested-name-specifier, as in:)A 
; : 161 2504 750 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2504 M 
-0.200 0 (        nested-name-specifier:)A 
; : 161 2549 1575 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2549 M 
-0.200 0 (           class-or-namespace-name :: nested-name-specifier opt)A 
; : 161 2594 1700 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2594 M 
-0.200 0 (     |     class-or-namespace-name :: template nested-name-specifier)A 
; : 161 2684 1850 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2684 M 
-0.200 0 (        so that any "template" keyword before the final \(unqualified\) name)A 
; : 161 2729 1850 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2729 M 
-0.200 0 (        is not part of the "nested-name-specifier", but is associated with)A 
; : 161 2774 1100 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2774 M 
-0.200 0 (        the unqualified name - as it is now.)A 
; : 161 2864 850 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2864 M 
-0.200 0 (        This allows the following:)A 
; : 161 2909 1150 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2909 M 
-0.200 0 (            A<T>::template B<X>::template C<Y>)A 
; : 161 2954 775 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2954 M 
-0.200 0 (                  -------------)A 
; : 161 3044 1575 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 3044 M 
-0.200 0 (     2.2\) Change the grammar for pseudo-destructor-name to say:)A 
; 
LH 
